00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:05,210 --> 00:00:06,578
Don't screw with me.

2
00:00:07,245 --> 00:00:09,481
Why did you just go and die on your own?

3
00:00:09,547 --> 00:00:12,383
If you're going to die,
tell us everything first.

4
00:00:12,450 --> 00:00:15,120
<i>Someone related to him</i>
<i>might know something.</i>

5
00:00:15,687 --> 00:00:17,155
<i>There must be a clue somewhere.</i>

6
00:00:19,757 --> 00:00:21,292
Is it a phone number?

7
00:00:23,995 --> 00:00:25,029
Hello.

8
00:00:25,096 --> 00:00:26,831
<i>Who is this?</i>

9
00:00:30,568 --> 00:00:31,936
Why are you picking up, Fumi…

10
00:00:33,705 --> 00:00:35,607
BREATHING MOUNTAINS
FUMI KARASHIMA PHOTO EXHIBIT

11
00:00:36,374 --> 00:00:37,342
Wait,

12
00:00:38,476 --> 00:00:39,611
are you Makoto?

13
00:00:40,278 --> 00:00:41,179
<i>Yes.</i>

14
00:00:41,813 --> 00:00:44,782
There’s something I want to ask.
Can we meet somewhere?

15
00:00:51,122 --> 00:00:53,358
Why are those two connected?

16
00:00:54,592 --> 00:00:56,294
We'll have to ask her directly.

17
00:00:57,128 --> 00:00:59,330
Maybe she even knows Tsuda’s motive.

18
00:01:00,565 --> 00:01:02,634
Is that key the only clue left?

19
00:01:07,272 --> 00:01:08,606
Hand it over.

20
00:01:08,673 --> 00:01:10,575
What you just put in your pocket.

21
00:01:13,411 --> 00:01:18,750
The Violent Crimes Division will keep that
until the bereaved family is located.

22
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:22,754
Take it without permission and
you'll be subject to disciplinary action.

23
00:01:27,392 --> 00:01:28,826
Don't do it.

24
00:01:28,893 --> 00:01:31,462
Searching any further is useless.

25
00:01:33,131 --> 00:01:34,132
Tsuda

26
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,635
didn't kill your parents.

27
00:01:40,205 --> 00:01:41,039
What?

28
00:01:41,839 --> 00:01:43,107
How do you know that?

29
00:01:48,713 --> 00:01:50,315
I never thought you brothers

30
00:01:52,283 --> 00:01:54,986
would end up becoming police officers.

31
00:01:57,188 --> 00:02:00,758
I used to be in the prefectural
police's First Division.

32
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:03,127
First Division?

33
00:02:05,029 --> 00:02:05,964
No way…

34
00:02:06,464 --> 00:02:09,133
I was chasing that case.

35
00:02:09,801 --> 00:02:12,203
<i>When will you catch them?</i>

36
00:02:12,971 --> 00:02:15,473
Why did my mom and dad die?

37
00:02:15,540 --> 00:02:20,445
1996

38
00:02:23,181 --> 00:02:25,116
You two were young back then.

39
00:02:27,452 --> 00:02:29,887
It's no wonder you didn't notice.

40
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:33,491
<i>Did you catch the killer?</i>

41
00:02:34,058 --> 00:02:38,363
I looked into it,
but it wasn't that person.

42
00:02:38,429 --> 00:02:39,264
What?

43
00:02:39,330 --> 00:02:41,466
1995

44
00:02:41,532 --> 00:02:44,002
But we, the police,

45
00:02:44,569 --> 00:02:48,640
will definitely catch the culprit.

46
00:03:08,293 --> 00:03:09,627
That night,

47
00:03:10,261 --> 00:03:13,331
Tsuda was called out
by someone from a publishing company

48
00:03:13,398 --> 00:03:16,100
and was drinking at a pub in Jimbocho.

49
00:03:17,001 --> 00:03:18,436
Maybe he faked an alibi?

50
00:03:18,503 --> 00:03:20,672
He said he would come
to our house that night.

51
00:03:20,738 --> 00:03:23,474
He was caught on a security camera.

52
00:03:23,541 --> 00:03:26,411
But the records back then
didn't mention it…

53
00:03:27,211 --> 00:03:30,448
A politician the Second Division
was tailing also appeared in that footage.

54
00:03:32,383 --> 00:03:34,018
To prevent it from leaking,

55
00:03:34,585 --> 00:03:40,558
the higher-ups decided not to report it
and just kept it an internal issue.

56
00:03:43,127 --> 00:03:46,864
I never imagined you guys
were still chasing Tsuda.

57
00:03:46,931 --> 00:03:49,600
If that's the case, why did he run away?

58
00:03:49,667 --> 00:03:51,969
If he’s innocent,
he had no need to disappear.

59
00:03:52,036 --> 00:03:54,138
He was removed from the list of suspects.

60
00:03:54,205 --> 00:03:56,240
You know the police
didn't look further into him.

61
00:03:58,710 --> 00:04:02,046
Is there anything else
you know about Tsuda?

62
00:04:04,782 --> 00:04:05,817
Mr. Koike!

63
00:04:09,654 --> 00:04:10,722
Tsuda

64
00:04:11,956 --> 00:04:16,494
might have been interviewing
people other than your father.

65
00:04:18,162 --> 00:04:19,597
Other people?

66
00:04:22,066 --> 00:04:24,235
The factory where the fire happened.

67
00:04:24,302 --> 00:04:26,204
1995, APRIL 26

68
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:28,706
<i>Apparently, he was sniffing</i>
<i>around that area.</i>

69
00:04:30,308 --> 00:04:33,511
I don't think it is relevant
to the case, though.

70
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:36,781
Give it.

71
00:04:38,916 --> 00:04:39,884
The key.

72
00:04:48,526 --> 00:04:50,628
-Help us out here.
-What?

73
00:04:50,695 --> 00:04:52,964
If there's a similar key,
they won't notice.

74
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:54,532
What are you guys--

75
00:04:54,599 --> 00:04:56,100
At least do that much for us.

76
00:04:56,801 --> 00:04:59,070
Since you didn't do anything
for us back then.

77
00:05:01,205 --> 00:05:03,674
The statute of limitations expired.

78
00:05:05,943 --> 00:05:08,346
What’s the point
of finding the culprit now?

79
00:05:08,413 --> 00:05:09,914
We want to know.

80
00:05:11,916 --> 00:05:13,985
Why were our parents killed?

81
00:05:17,255 --> 00:05:21,125
We won't cause you any more trouble.

82
00:05:24,162 --> 00:05:29,133
LAND FOR LEASE AS CAR PARK, STORAGE, ETC.

83
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:32,970
If he was investigating the factory,
that explains why he knows Fumi.

84
00:05:33,704 --> 00:05:36,140
What was Tsuda investigating?

85
00:05:40,244 --> 00:05:43,347
Seems after the fire,
the land here was sold off.

86
00:05:44,749 --> 00:05:48,152
But it’s not like everything is gone.

87
00:05:49,454 --> 00:05:51,122
If it’s not Tsuda,

88
00:05:53,157 --> 00:05:55,593
the culprit is still out there somewhere.

89
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:08,873
<i>I'm Kawano from the Akita Police.</i>
<i>Please, go ahead.</i>

90
00:06:09,907 --> 00:06:11,042
Let’s get started then.

91
00:06:12,109 --> 00:06:14,545
Resident Aiko Mizusawa
was killed in an arson-murder

92
00:06:14,612 --> 00:06:16,514
at her apartment in the Kanagawa Ward.

93
00:06:16,581 --> 00:06:20,284
Gold bars worth 100 million yen
were found in the residence.

94
00:06:20,351 --> 00:06:23,921
After verification,
they matched the gold bars

95
00:06:23,988 --> 00:06:27,391
from the 400 million yen robbery
that occurred in Akita a year ago.

96
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:28,960
There were four robbers.

97
00:06:29,026 --> 00:06:32,830
Was Aiko Mizusawa's name
on the suspect list?

98
00:06:32,897 --> 00:06:36,434
<i>No, she wasn't listed here.</i>

99
00:06:36,501 --> 00:06:38,736
There's testimony that before her death,

100
00:06:38,803 --> 00:06:42,440
Mizusawa was being stalked
by a man named Togo.

101
00:06:43,007 --> 00:06:46,410
He is thought to be either
one of the robbers, or the mastermind.

102
00:06:46,477 --> 00:06:49,080
Do you have any information on him?

103
00:06:50,014 --> 00:06:52,383
<i>We have no information at this time.</i>

104
00:06:53,217 --> 00:06:56,621
<i>Are you saying that</i>
<i>this Togo man is the arsonist?</i>

105
00:06:56,687 --> 00:06:59,724
No, the one who set the fire
is likely Yugo Hiranaka.

106
00:07:00,458 --> 00:07:02,193
<i>Yugo Hiranaka?</i>

107
00:07:02,727 --> 00:07:04,195
Flyers used to start the fire

108
00:07:04,262 --> 00:07:06,898
were only distributed around
where Hiranaka lives.

109
00:07:07,665 --> 00:07:09,901
Hiranaka also had a bruise on his neck

110
00:07:09,967 --> 00:07:12,870
that closely resembled the tattoo
of one of the four robbers.

111
00:07:12,937 --> 00:07:17,174
Hiranaka and Togo might have been
chasing Mizusawa together.

112
00:07:17,842 --> 00:07:20,811
However, Hiranaka fled by car.

113
00:07:20,878 --> 00:07:22,680
<i>We are currently tracking him.</i>

114
00:07:26,017 --> 00:07:28,619
Did Hiranaka flee in a panic?

115
00:07:28,686 --> 00:07:31,689
His smartphone is turned off, right?

116
00:07:31,756 --> 00:07:32,690
Yes.

117
00:07:32,757 --> 00:07:35,493
It’s difficult to pinpoint his location
via cell signal.

118
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,929
He lives in a nice house.

119
00:07:43,568 --> 00:07:44,535
Yes.

120
00:07:45,603 --> 00:07:46,504
Right.

121
00:07:51,409 --> 00:07:54,712
Do you think he left and met up with Togo?

122
00:07:54,779 --> 00:07:56,747
They’re probably overseas by now.

123
00:07:57,248 --> 00:07:58,683
Such shallow logic.

124
00:07:59,884 --> 00:08:00,918
-What?
-Oh, no.

125
00:08:00,985 --> 00:08:02,853
-What did you just say?
-That hurts.

126
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,055
-I'm sorry.
-Hey.

127
00:08:04,121 --> 00:08:05,256
Hey.

128
00:08:06,757 --> 00:08:08,593
They found

129
00:08:10,027 --> 00:08:11,395
Yugo Hiranaka's body.

130
00:08:12,697 --> 00:08:13,564
What?

131
00:08:16,133 --> 00:08:17,935
One, two, three.

132
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:20,304
There.

133
00:08:20,371 --> 00:08:21,906
-Scale.
-Here.

134
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:26,911
Nine stab wounds were confirmed
on the back of the body.

135
00:08:27,645 --> 00:08:31,749
The fatal wound was a stab
below the right shoulder blade.

136
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:36,287
The blade pierced the lungs,
causing air and blood to fill the chest.

137
00:08:36,354 --> 00:08:39,023
The culprit must have had a strong grudge.

138
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:41,258
Dr. Kagura.

139
00:08:41,325 --> 00:08:43,661
There’s a variation
in the depth of the wounds.

140
00:08:44,395 --> 00:08:47,732
They range from six centimeters
to 14 centimeters at the deepest.

141
00:08:48,766 --> 00:08:50,134
What about the angle?

142
00:08:50,935 --> 00:08:52,670
The blade was inserted like this…

143
00:08:53,337 --> 00:08:54,438
Almost vertically.

144
00:08:56,374 --> 00:08:57,541
I see.

145
00:09:09,787 --> 00:09:11,322
What’s bothering you?

146
00:09:11,822 --> 00:09:13,190
The force of the stabs.

147
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:17,428
If there’s a strong intent to kill,
the blade is usually plunged in deep.

148
00:09:17,495 --> 00:09:20,164
But the body had several
shallow wounds as well.

149
00:09:20,665 --> 00:09:23,200
-In cases like this…
-They were probably in a hurry.

150
00:09:23,934 --> 00:09:25,970
Maybe someone was coming.

151
00:09:26,837 --> 00:09:29,140
Repeated stabbing in a short time?

152
00:09:29,206 --> 00:09:32,309
Repeated stabbing would cause
the depth of the wounds to vary.

153
00:09:35,713 --> 00:09:39,650
The man killed at the marina
is Yugo Hiranaka, 23 years old.

154
00:09:39,717 --> 00:09:42,787
An investor who owns several
properties within the prefecture.

155
00:09:42,853 --> 00:09:46,223
His legal residence was Akita Prefecture,
the same as Aiko Mizusawa.

156
00:09:46,991 --> 00:09:49,427
Hiranaka suffered neglect as a child

157
00:09:49,493 --> 00:09:51,696
and was reportedly estranged
from his parents.

158
00:09:51,762 --> 00:09:54,532
This photo was found at his home.

159
00:09:54,598 --> 00:09:56,300
It also shows Aiko Mizusawa

160
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:59,704
and a person believed
to be her friend, Saki Yokokura.

161
00:09:59,770 --> 00:10:03,407
Hiranaka started investing one year ago,

162
00:10:03,474 --> 00:10:06,143
immediately after the gold robbery.

163
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:08,112
Like Aiko Mizusawa,

164
00:10:08,646 --> 00:10:12,983
Hiranaka may have used
the gold bars he made off with.

165
00:10:13,517 --> 00:10:14,552
The autopsy results?

166
00:10:15,119 --> 00:10:19,023
On Yugo Hiranaka's body,
we found no defensive wounds.

167
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:21,125
Does that mean he knew the suspect?

168
00:10:21,692 --> 00:10:23,227
We don't know that yet.

169
00:10:23,828 --> 00:10:26,897
The moment of the crime
was not caught on security cameras,

170
00:10:26,964 --> 00:10:28,733
but a person carrying a suitcase

171
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:31,602
was sighted near the marina
at the same time.

172
00:10:32,269 --> 00:10:33,971
Is this man Togo?

173
00:10:34,038 --> 00:10:37,074
The motive for the crime
was likely the suitcase.

174
00:10:37,575 --> 00:10:40,511
The case the man is holding
belonged to Hiranaka.

175
00:10:42,413 --> 00:10:45,116
The contents might be
the rest of the gold bars.

176
00:10:45,182 --> 00:10:47,752
It's possible they had
a falling out, and he took it.

177
00:10:48,719 --> 00:10:50,488
The robbers were a group of four.

178
00:10:50,554 --> 00:10:53,491
It's hard to believe
it’s just a coincidence.

179
00:10:54,258 --> 00:10:57,895
It's possible this Yuzuru boy's
family name is Togo.

180
00:10:57,962 --> 00:11:00,998
Continue to search for witnesses, and…

181
00:11:01,665 --> 00:11:04,301
investigate Saki Yokokura
as a person of interest.

182
00:11:04,368 --> 00:11:05,536
Yes, sir!

183
00:11:07,605 --> 00:11:10,541
BATHHOUSE

184
00:11:11,475 --> 00:11:13,377
This place hasn't changed.

185
00:11:14,512 --> 00:11:16,580
Man, I'm hungry.

186
00:11:18,549 --> 00:11:19,683
But…

187
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:21,752
I just don't get it.

188
00:11:21,819 --> 00:11:22,887
Get what?

189
00:11:23,621 --> 00:11:24,688
Why Hiranaka

190
00:11:24,755 --> 00:11:28,292
went as far as to set fire to the house
of his childhood friend, Aiko Mizusawa.

191
00:11:29,059 --> 00:11:30,127
Hey.

192
00:11:30,194 --> 00:11:32,062
I'm off the clock right now.

193
00:11:32,129 --> 00:11:35,766
Maybe he was told to kill her, to be
forgiven for running off with the gold.

194
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:39,370
I just felt refreshed,
don't bring up such heavy topics.

195
00:11:39,436 --> 00:11:41,906
And then he was betrayed
and killed by Togo.

196
00:11:43,741 --> 00:11:46,977
Did the gold bars destroy the relationship
the four of them had?

197
00:11:48,345 --> 00:11:51,749
We just have to find
one of the people in that photo.

198
00:11:52,683 --> 00:11:53,751
What about Saki Yokokura?

199
00:11:55,653 --> 00:11:56,854
She vanished.

200
00:11:57,621 --> 00:12:01,492
<i>When First Division went, the room</i>
<i>was ransacked, and bloodstains were found.</i>

201
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:03,394
-Check the security cameras.
-Yes.

202
00:12:05,129 --> 00:12:07,331
That might be Togo's doing as well.

203
00:12:08,365 --> 00:12:11,368
Did he kidnap her
to find out where the gold is?

204
00:12:12,436 --> 00:12:15,339
It's too early to be certain,
but you should hurry up and go.

205
00:12:15,406 --> 00:12:16,340
What?

206
00:12:17,474 --> 00:12:18,542
To Akita.

207
00:12:20,477 --> 00:12:22,112
What a pain.

208
00:12:24,114 --> 00:12:25,549
Mogi, gyoza.

209
00:12:25,616 --> 00:12:26,617
For two.

210
00:12:30,688 --> 00:12:33,691
What happened to the man named Tsuda?

211
00:12:37,761 --> 00:12:39,029
He died of an illness.

212
00:12:40,931 --> 00:12:43,500
We didn't get
any info out of him in the end.

213
00:12:47,071 --> 00:12:47,905
I see.

214
00:12:47,972 --> 00:12:49,039
But…

215
00:12:51,475 --> 00:12:52,543
it's not over yet.

216
00:12:55,846 --> 00:12:56,780
Minoru.

217
00:12:57,948 --> 00:12:59,083
I'll leave it to you.

218
00:13:00,985 --> 00:13:01,852
Sure.

219
00:13:11,762 --> 00:13:14,999
KARASHIMA

220
00:13:20,337 --> 00:13:21,438
Welcome.

221
00:13:22,806 --> 00:13:23,974
It has been a while.

222
00:13:26,076 --> 00:13:27,044
Minoru?

223
00:13:47,231 --> 00:13:48,565
Here you go.

224
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:52,903
Makoto had to go to Akita
on a sudden business trip.

225
00:13:53,470 --> 00:13:56,307
I see. Sounds like he's doing well.

226
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,943
Fumi, how have you been since then?

227
00:13:59,476 --> 00:14:04,748
I underwent surgery,
and steadily continued with my rehab…

228
00:14:04,815 --> 00:14:07,351
Is that how you're able to take
photos of mountains again?

229
00:14:07,851 --> 00:14:09,720
I'm still full of energy, you know.

230
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:12,056
I'm going climbing again next week.

231
00:14:14,591 --> 00:14:15,893
Back then,

232
00:14:17,161 --> 00:14:19,596
I had almost given up,
thinking it was impossible.

233
00:14:20,531 --> 00:14:24,234
It’s amazing that you’re even holding
a solo exhibition now.

234
00:14:24,301 --> 00:14:26,737
Oh, you know a lot.

235
00:14:26,804 --> 00:14:28,572
I looked you up online.

236
00:14:37,414 --> 00:14:38,615
So, what is it today?

237
00:14:40,951 --> 00:14:42,453
You wanted to ask me something?

238
00:14:46,623 --> 00:14:49,026
You know a man
named Yuji Tsuda, don't you?

239
00:14:49,927 --> 00:14:50,794
Tsuda?

240
00:14:51,729 --> 00:14:54,598
He used to write nonfiction books.

241
00:14:54,665 --> 00:14:55,899
An author.

242
00:14:55,966 --> 00:14:57,968
YUJI TSUDA
VOICES OF THE DEAD

243
00:14:58,035 --> 00:15:02,373
I don't know anyone like that.

244
00:15:02,439 --> 00:15:05,275
But he had your number, Fumi.

245
00:15:06,310 --> 00:15:07,244
Mine?

246
00:15:09,079 --> 00:15:10,347
Before the incident,

247
00:15:11,215 --> 00:15:13,717
did this man ever visit you?

248
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,691
I'm sorry.

249
00:15:21,992 --> 00:15:25,496
Back then, I avoided meeting people.

250
00:15:36,907 --> 00:15:38,542
It's nice to see you again.

251
00:15:41,412 --> 00:15:43,547
Darling, this is Minoru.

252
00:15:43,614 --> 00:15:45,816
You know, from the Tagusaris.

253
00:15:53,123 --> 00:15:56,026
Excuse me, could I ask you
a few questions?

254
00:16:00,597 --> 00:16:03,734
He hasn't been feeling well lately.

255
00:16:05,569 --> 00:16:07,571
I'm sorry, Minoru.

256
00:16:14,411 --> 00:16:18,515
-Want to call the Japan Auto Federation?
-You idiot. How can the police call JAF?

257
00:16:20,284 --> 00:16:21,585
This will take some time.

258
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,488
Is it close by?

259
00:16:24,555 --> 00:16:25,856
Right there.

260
00:16:25,923 --> 00:16:29,293
But Asami Town is a big place.

261
00:16:29,359 --> 00:16:31,695
We can't do much with just that photo.

262
00:16:32,763 --> 00:16:35,332
I'm sure he didn't want to go home,

263
00:16:35,399 --> 00:16:37,968
so he would be looking
for a place to stay nearby.

264
00:16:38,035 --> 00:16:39,403
Like a park?

265
00:16:39,903 --> 00:16:40,904
He won't be outside.

266
00:16:40,971 --> 00:16:43,707
-He would be caught immediately.
-Oh, right.

267
00:16:45,042 --> 00:16:48,579
The best place would be
somewhere he can get a meal

268
00:16:48,645 --> 00:16:50,914
even if he doesn't have money.

269
00:16:51,849 --> 00:16:54,084
I think I know a place like that.

270
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:58,255
CHILDREN'S CANTEEN

271
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:01,992
This is definitely the place.

272
00:17:05,429 --> 00:17:07,931
Do these children look familiar to you?

273
00:17:10,134 --> 00:17:12,302
How nostalgic.

274
00:17:12,369 --> 00:17:13,537
Do you know them?

275
00:17:13,604 --> 00:17:17,341
Yeah. All four of them
had a lot of trouble with their parents.

276
00:17:17,841 --> 00:17:21,545
They moved from place to place
and came here around the same time.

277
00:17:21,612 --> 00:17:23,146
Were they close?

278
00:17:23,213 --> 00:17:26,183
They were always together
when they were here.

279
00:17:26,917 --> 00:17:29,620
<i>They often talked about</i>

280
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,689
<i>how they wanted to open</i>
<i>a shop together someday.</i>

281
00:17:32,756 --> 00:17:34,324
<i>They wanted children like them,</i>

282
00:17:34,892 --> 00:17:37,794
<i>who were facing various hardships,</i>
<i>to be able to come there.</i>

283
00:17:41,565 --> 00:17:43,834
Are you in contact with those four?

284
00:17:43,901 --> 00:17:45,569
No, not now.

285
00:17:46,637 --> 00:17:50,340
But Yuzuru stops by every now and then.

286
00:17:50,407 --> 00:17:51,975
Is it Yuzuru Togo?

287
00:17:52,676 --> 00:17:55,679
No, it's Yoshimoto. Yuzuru Yoshimoto.

288
00:17:56,813 --> 00:17:58,549
Have you ever heard the name Togo?

289
00:17:59,416 --> 00:18:02,152
I don't think so…

290
00:18:02,219 --> 00:18:06,256
Then, do you know
where Yuzuru Yoshimoto is?

291
00:18:07,224 --> 00:18:10,727
Oh, he's been visiting
his mother's nursing home.

292
00:18:11,728 --> 00:18:15,365
That woman in the wheelchair
is Yuzuru Yoshimoto's mother.

293
00:18:15,432 --> 00:18:17,401
I heard she was ill…

294
00:18:17,935 --> 00:18:20,170
She has always had a chronic illness,

295
00:18:20,237 --> 00:18:23,106
and Yuzuru has been
caring for her until now.

296
00:18:26,076 --> 00:18:29,680
This nursing home looks awfully pricey.

297
00:18:45,295 --> 00:18:46,396
I'm home.

298
00:18:56,740 --> 00:18:57,641
A souvenir.

299
00:18:58,709 --> 00:19:01,578
-Isn't it just from a convenience store?
-One in Akita!

300
00:19:01,645 --> 00:19:02,746
They're all the same.

301
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:06,250
I even found the gummies you like!

302
00:19:09,286 --> 00:19:10,554
How was Fumi?

303
00:19:16,093 --> 00:19:17,227
Was it no good?

304
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:22,165
She hadn't been in contact with Tsuda.

305
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:25,669
I couldn't talk
to the factory manager either.

306
00:19:31,775 --> 00:19:34,711
Why was Tsuda looking into that factory?

307
00:19:36,146 --> 00:19:38,482
Does it have anything to do with the case?

308
00:19:40,083 --> 00:19:41,551
I have no idea at all.

309
00:19:44,521 --> 00:19:45,589
What about the key?

310
00:19:46,156 --> 00:19:48,659
They say it's used for lockers,
desk drawers, padlocks…

311
00:19:48,725 --> 00:19:50,994
<i>All sorts of things.</i>
<i>It's a very common type.</i>

312
00:19:52,929 --> 00:19:55,098
At this rate, even if we had 100 years…

313
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:58,068
What about Dad's desk?

314
00:20:00,637 --> 00:20:03,607
The drawer of that desk was always locked.

315
00:20:05,108 --> 00:20:06,143
Then…

316
00:20:06,877 --> 00:20:09,012
it might be related to the factory.

317
00:20:19,456 --> 00:20:23,226
Next week, I'll be going to Hida.

318
00:20:29,466 --> 00:20:30,634
It will be okay.

319
00:20:33,036 --> 00:20:35,839
You don't have to worry about a thing.

320
00:20:47,718 --> 00:20:49,019
How was Akita?

321
00:20:49,853 --> 00:20:51,988
The last of the four is Yuzuru Yoshimoto.

322
00:20:52,055 --> 00:20:53,423
It wasn't Togo.

323
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:54,324
What?

324
00:20:54,391 --> 00:20:56,093
Togo is likely the mastermind.

325
00:20:57,561 --> 00:21:00,564
Probably chased down the four
who ran off with the gold.

326
00:21:00,630 --> 00:21:02,866
Then, isn't Yoshimoto in danger?

327
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:05,102
Yoshimoto also lives in Kanagawa,

328
00:21:05,168 --> 00:21:07,504
and the police are currently
staking out his home.

329
00:21:07,571 --> 00:21:10,774
They plan to wait until morning,
then take him into custody.

330
00:21:14,978 --> 00:21:15,979
But…

331
00:21:17,547 --> 00:21:19,282
maybe we should've left them alone.

332
00:21:20,684 --> 00:21:21,718
Why?

333
00:21:22,285 --> 00:21:24,154
Yoshimoto is a young caregiver,

334
00:21:25,021 --> 00:21:27,657
and Yokokura's father was in debt.

335
00:21:32,562 --> 00:21:35,732
They must've been desperate to survive.

336
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:38,168
Even as kids.

337
00:21:44,508 --> 00:21:45,442
I suppose so.

338
00:21:55,919 --> 00:21:58,822
No one came to visit Yoshimoto.

339
00:22:00,791 --> 00:22:04,294
Togo isn't showing up either.

340
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:08,765
I wonder if Saki Yokokura is okay?

341
00:22:09,866 --> 00:22:12,869
First Division is chasing it,
but hasn't found her yet.

342
00:22:12,936 --> 00:22:14,771
The apartment's security camera?

343
00:22:15,338 --> 00:22:17,674
Apparently, the whole
camera unit was taken.

344
00:22:22,212 --> 00:22:24,915
The four of them
all ran to Kanagawa, only for this…

345
00:22:28,385 --> 00:22:30,787
It's because they were stupid
and robbed people.

346
00:22:34,991 --> 00:22:35,926
He's out.

347
00:22:45,869 --> 00:22:47,704
You're Yuzuru Yoshimoto, right?

348
00:22:50,006 --> 00:22:51,541
Guess I don't even need to ask.

349
00:22:53,276 --> 00:22:55,212
Please come with us to the station.

350
00:22:55,278 --> 00:22:56,680
I was deceived.

351
00:22:58,181 --> 00:22:59,416
What do you mean by that?

352
00:23:00,183 --> 00:23:02,352
Saki called me.

353
00:23:02,419 --> 00:23:04,020
<i>The four of us will steal gold.</i>

354
00:23:04,688 --> 00:23:07,557
I was invited by a man named Togo.
He's the mastermind.

355
00:23:07,624 --> 00:23:11,461
He said the owner just wants to pretend
the gold was stolen, for tax purposes.

356
00:23:12,329 --> 00:23:14,831
Togo said the police
wouldn't even chase us.

357
00:23:16,733 --> 00:23:18,435
It's a fake robbery!

358
00:23:18,969 --> 00:23:22,539
The reward was 300,000 yen per person.

359
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:24,341
What?

360
00:23:25,475 --> 00:23:27,511
You would commit robbery
for such a small amount?

361
00:23:28,678 --> 00:23:32,315
We didn't think we would get caught.

362
00:23:32,382 --> 00:23:34,384
And for us, that was enough.

363
00:23:35,986 --> 00:23:37,754
With 300,000 yen,

364
00:23:39,422 --> 00:23:41,691
I could hire a caregiver for my mother.

365
00:23:43,894 --> 00:23:45,395
Even if only for a short time,

366
00:23:46,096 --> 00:23:48,164
I could finally be free.

367
00:23:49,866 --> 00:23:54,237
In reality, you ended up being chased
by the police and Togo.

368
00:23:55,605 --> 00:23:57,407
We had no choice but to run!

369
00:24:01,044 --> 00:24:03,013
Hey, Kudo.

370
00:24:10,854 --> 00:24:12,155
When that happens,

371
00:24:13,256 --> 00:24:14,491
you turn yourself in.

372
00:24:17,093 --> 00:24:17,994
Let's go.

373
00:24:38,615 --> 00:24:39,716
Thank you.

374
00:24:42,085 --> 00:24:45,121
After fleeing from Akita,
they turned the gold into cash.

375
00:24:45,755 --> 00:24:49,326
It seems there was
an unlicensed pawnshop in Yokohama.

376
00:24:50,126 --> 00:24:52,796
They each took 100 million
to pay off debts.

377
00:24:52,862 --> 00:24:54,731
or put their parents in facilities.

378
00:24:55,298 --> 00:24:57,934
They were finally liberated
from their parents.

379
00:24:58,735 --> 00:25:01,404
And Togo deceived those four?

380
00:25:03,239 --> 00:25:05,375
Can we trace Togo
through Yuzuru Yoshimoto?

381
00:25:05,909 --> 00:25:06,743
No.

382
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:09,779
He says he never met him
or even contacted him.

383
00:25:10,981 --> 00:25:15,986
So in the end, the only connection
is Saki Yokokura, who was kidnapped.

384
00:25:18,188 --> 00:25:20,123
-Thank you!
-Thanks for the meal.

385
00:25:25,362 --> 00:25:27,330
Oh, what do you want, Haruko?

386
00:25:27,397 --> 00:25:28,398
A beer, please.

387
00:25:28,465 --> 00:25:29,299
Sure thing.

388
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:32,302
I heard from Minoru.

389
00:25:32,936 --> 00:25:34,404
He said Tsuda is dead.

390
00:25:35,171 --> 00:25:38,541
He said, they didn't get
anything out of him in the end.

391
00:25:40,443 --> 00:25:41,277
Yeah.

392
00:25:44,514 --> 00:25:45,348
Here.

393
00:25:45,415 --> 00:25:47,283
This is on the house.

394
00:25:47,917 --> 00:25:50,286
Wow, how nostalgic.

395
00:25:50,353 --> 00:25:52,355
Mogi's fried rice!

396
00:25:53,123 --> 00:25:55,825
Do you remember it? Minoru’s birthday.

397
00:25:56,426 --> 00:25:57,694
How could I forget?

398
00:25:58,795 --> 00:26:01,331
<i>I put candles in the fried rice.</i>

399
00:26:02,365 --> 00:26:04,634
<i>How did you ever think of that?</i>

400
00:26:04,701 --> 00:26:06,636
<i>I just wanted to do something for him.</i>

401
00:26:06,703 --> 00:26:09,806
At that time, we couldn't afford
to buy a cake.

402
00:26:10,407 --> 00:26:13,943
But, he looked so incredibly happy.

403
00:26:15,945 --> 00:26:19,115
Back then, they were like
ordinary kids you would see anywhere.

404
00:26:24,621 --> 00:26:26,690
But I suppose I was wrong.

405
00:26:28,992 --> 00:26:31,895
If I had stayed close to them
and supported them,

406
00:26:31,961 --> 00:26:33,997
they might have had a different future.

407
00:26:35,532 --> 00:26:38,768
By now, Minoru would have become
a forensic scientist, and Makoto…

408
00:26:38,835 --> 00:26:40,103
What are you saying?

409
00:26:40,804 --> 00:26:42,706
You supported them well.

410
00:26:49,779 --> 00:26:53,216
I hope one day,
we can laugh like that again.

411
00:26:56,019 --> 00:26:56,953
Yeah.

412
00:27:02,792 --> 00:27:04,260
I knew I would find you here.

413
00:27:07,697 --> 00:27:10,400
I went to the shop
to try to sell you this.

414
00:27:10,967 --> 00:27:14,604
VOICES OF THE DEAD

415
00:27:18,742 --> 00:27:20,009
Is this Tsuda's?

416
00:27:21,578 --> 00:27:23,413
I don't need it anymore.

417
00:27:26,950 --> 00:27:29,586
You mean there's another culprit
besides Tsuda?

418
00:27:30,186 --> 00:27:31,855
Isn't there anything you can remember?

419
00:27:38,528 --> 00:27:41,064
<i>You're the only one who saw the culprit.</i>

420
00:27:43,867 --> 00:27:45,235
It was dark,

421
00:27:46,069 --> 00:27:48,304
and they were wearing a hood and a mask.

422
00:27:50,273 --> 00:27:51,241
I'm sorry.

423
00:27:52,041 --> 00:27:53,543
I've asked you so many times.

424
00:27:56,646 --> 00:27:58,615
So you have no clues at all.

425
00:27:59,415 --> 00:28:00,250
No…

426
00:28:03,119 --> 00:28:04,420
There's one thing left.

427
00:28:18,168 --> 00:28:19,235
Haruko.

428
00:28:20,804 --> 00:28:22,438
Introduce me to a good pawnshop.

429
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:26,309
If you're looking for a fight,
I'll fight you.

430
00:28:26,376 --> 00:28:28,711
Do you know a shop
in Yokohama called Suiren-do?

431
00:28:34,551 --> 00:28:36,753
That place was flagged by police,

432
00:28:36,820 --> 00:28:39,355
and its owner fled back
to his country six months ago.

433
00:28:39,422 --> 00:28:42,325
That's why I want to know
about shops that "cross the line."

434
00:28:44,027 --> 00:28:47,130
You can't keep gold bars
with a trail on them forever.

435
00:28:47,797 --> 00:28:49,666
Togo must want to cash them out.

436
00:28:53,570 --> 00:28:56,072
There's no time. Hurry up.

437
00:28:58,308 --> 00:29:00,009
I can't tell you anything, Makoto.

438
00:29:00,743 --> 00:29:01,644
What?

439
00:29:02,512 --> 00:29:05,014
Sorry, but I can't sell out my colleagues.

440
00:29:05,081 --> 00:29:06,382
Look into it yourselves.

441
00:29:06,449 --> 00:29:07,984
Haruko.

442
00:29:08,051 --> 00:29:10,320
We have our own rules over here!

443
00:29:16,926 --> 00:29:19,562
YUGO HIRANAKA MURDER CASE AUTOPSY RESULTS

444
00:29:19,629 --> 00:29:22,498
Are these the forensics results
for Yugo Hiranaka?

445
00:29:22,565 --> 00:29:23,600
Yes.

446
00:29:24,334 --> 00:29:26,469
I read Yuzuru Yoshimoto's statement.

447
00:29:26,536 --> 00:29:29,072
He says Hiranaka had no prior
connection with Togo.

448
00:29:29,906 --> 00:29:31,341
If they weren't acquaintances,

449
00:29:31,407 --> 00:29:33,543
the footprints
in the parking lot bother me.

450
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:35,411
Footprints?

451
00:29:35,478 --> 00:29:38,615
Because it was raining, only the
footprints in the perimeter remained,

452
00:29:39,349 --> 00:29:43,620
but Togo's stride is clearly shorter
than Hiranaka's.

453
00:29:43,686 --> 00:29:44,587
What?

454
00:29:45,088 --> 00:29:48,024
Please send Togo's security footage
for gait analysis.

455
00:29:48,091 --> 00:29:50,693
But we can't identify
without a subject for comparison.

456
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,095
I don't mind.

457
00:29:52,161 --> 00:29:54,430
I just want to know more about their gait.

458
00:29:54,497 --> 00:29:55,465
On it.

459
00:29:56,399 --> 00:29:59,469
KAWADA PAWNSHOP

460
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:02,505
He might have already cashed it in.

461
00:30:05,174 --> 00:30:08,745
It has been three days
since Togo ran off with Hiranaka's gold.

462
00:30:08,811 --> 00:30:13,016
Even if Yokokura still had her gold left,
she was kidnapped two days ago.

463
00:30:21,057 --> 00:30:22,025
Hello?

464
00:30:22,525 --> 00:30:24,460
<i>That shop wasn't it, huh?</i>

465
00:30:25,895 --> 00:30:28,097
If you're messing with me, I'm hanging up.

466
00:30:28,164 --> 00:30:31,301
<i>It seems a certain pawnshop</i>
<i>just received some gold bars.</i>

467
00:30:31,968 --> 00:30:32,635
What?

468
00:30:33,603 --> 00:30:36,205
I asked shops I know to contact me
if something comes up.

469
00:30:37,540 --> 00:30:39,842
Connections are important, you know.

470
00:30:40,977 --> 00:30:43,146
If you don't hurry, you won't catch them.

471
00:30:43,212 --> 00:30:46,215
The shop's name is Kiho in Yokohama.

472
00:30:49,719 --> 00:30:50,620
Drive!

473
00:30:50,687 --> 00:30:51,721
Yes.

474
00:30:59,062 --> 00:31:01,064
I wonder if Togo is still at the shop.

475
00:31:02,231 --> 00:31:03,066
What's wrong?

476
00:31:03,633 --> 00:31:05,601
The variance in the depths of the wounds…

477
00:31:05,668 --> 00:31:08,471
-It's due to a lack of muscle strength.
<i>-What?</i>

478
00:31:08,538 --> 00:31:11,607
After analyzing Togo's gait
on the camera footage,

479
00:31:11,674 --> 00:31:13,810
there is an approximately 90% probability…

480
00:31:15,778 --> 00:31:17,313
that Togo is a woman.

481
00:31:22,118 --> 00:31:24,020
KIHO PAWNSHOP

482
00:31:26,622 --> 00:31:27,657
Mr. Tagusari?

483
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:44,807
Yokokura.

484
00:31:52,849 --> 00:31:53,883
Oh, no…

485
00:31:54,450 --> 00:31:55,351
I'm busted, aren't I?

486
00:31:59,022 --> 00:32:01,424
I went to the trouble
of cutting my own arm, too.

487
00:32:08,364 --> 00:32:09,732
Can I have a smoke?

488
00:32:10,533 --> 00:32:11,501
Since it's my last.

489
00:32:19,542 --> 00:32:21,344
You're Togo, aren't you?

490
00:32:27,350 --> 00:32:28,718
Togo was…

491
00:32:31,988 --> 00:32:34,490
the debt collector
who used to come to our house.

492
00:32:35,491 --> 00:32:36,993
Every single day…

493
00:32:37,627 --> 00:32:40,730
he would bang on the door,
saying, "Pay back the money!"

494
00:32:42,165 --> 00:32:46,803
That voice got stuck in my ears,
so I ended up using his name.

495
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:52,542
So from the beginning,

496
00:32:53,309 --> 00:32:55,445
there never was a man named Togo.

497
00:32:59,015 --> 00:33:01,417
Aiko Mizusawa realized that, didn't she?

498
00:33:03,453 --> 00:33:04,554
That girl…

499
00:33:05,521 --> 00:33:09,425
for someone so unfriendly,
her intuition was sharp.

500
00:33:11,794 --> 00:33:12,695
Hey.

501
00:33:12,762 --> 00:33:13,963
Togo…

502
00:33:14,997 --> 00:33:16,732
doesn't actually exist, does he?

503
00:33:17,733 --> 00:33:18,568
What?

504
00:33:18,634 --> 00:33:21,838
Saki, you made him up.

505
00:33:24,740 --> 00:33:27,343
<i>I tried to make it seem</i>
<i>like a misunderstanding.</i>

506
00:33:27,910 --> 00:33:31,814
<i>I told Yugo that Aiko</i>
<i>was planning to betray us.</i>

507
00:33:31,881 --> 00:33:34,750
You mean Aiko is trying
to turn herself in?

508
00:33:35,485 --> 00:33:37,186
If we threaten her a little,

509
00:33:38,187 --> 00:33:40,423
Aiko might change her mind.

510
00:33:41,057 --> 00:33:43,659
<i>We thought if we set the fire</i>
<i>while I was at work,</i>

511
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:47,430
<i>we could make Aiko believe Togo existed.</i>

512
00:33:49,565 --> 00:33:52,802
<i>I never imagined she would be home.</i>

513
00:33:53,536 --> 00:33:54,704
<i>The police are here.</i>

514
00:33:54,770 --> 00:33:56,239
<i>We can't run anymore.</i>

515
00:33:57,039 --> 00:34:00,009
That was an accident. It's not your fault.

516
00:34:00,076 --> 00:34:01,711
<i>I'm going to turn myself in.</i>

517
00:34:01,777 --> 00:34:03,746
<i>I have to tell them</i>
<i>I thought Aiko wasn't--</i>

518
00:34:03,813 --> 00:34:04,747
Wait a minute.

519
00:34:06,716 --> 00:34:09,051
I'm going to the police
to tell them everything.

520
00:34:11,687 --> 00:34:13,890
<i>There was no turning back anymore.</i>

521
00:34:24,967 --> 00:34:26,936
I don't particularly have any regrets.

522
00:34:45,321 --> 00:34:46,622
I wish I had been born

523
00:34:48,191 --> 00:34:50,026
into a house like that.

524
00:34:53,062 --> 00:34:55,398
The children at that canteen

525
00:34:56,465 --> 00:34:59,001
all needed money.

526
00:35:03,839 --> 00:35:05,775
We had to either live without dreams

527
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:09,645
or do bad stuff.

528
00:35:13,149 --> 00:35:14,183
But…

529
00:35:15,952 --> 00:35:18,187
if you have money, everything changes.

530
00:35:19,422 --> 00:35:20,990
As long as you have money…

531
00:35:21,791 --> 00:35:23,259
And how did that turn out?

532
00:35:26,128 --> 00:35:27,663
Once you got the money,

533
00:35:28,965 --> 00:35:30,333
did it go as you planned?

534
00:35:33,536 --> 00:35:35,271
The reason I turned out like this

535
00:35:36,872 --> 00:35:38,674
is all because of my parents.

536
00:35:42,778 --> 00:35:44,280
It’s all your fault.

537
00:35:46,082 --> 00:35:48,718
"If not for you,
I wouldn't have suffered like this."

538
00:35:52,588 --> 00:35:56,325
All worthless parents
say that to their children.

539
00:35:58,361 --> 00:35:59,528
But…

540
00:35:59,595 --> 00:36:03,532
because those kids don't want to trouble
their parents, they can't ask for help.

541
00:36:06,469 --> 00:36:09,272
Even when told,
"I wish I had never given birth to you,"

542
00:36:09,939 --> 00:36:11,874
they still can't abandon their parents.

543
00:36:17,580 --> 00:36:19,048
It’s pathetic, isn't it?

544
00:36:38,701 --> 00:36:40,469
She confessed to the crimes.

545
00:36:41,270 --> 00:36:42,171
I see.

546
00:36:44,874 --> 00:36:45,908
That vehicle…

547
00:36:49,512 --> 00:36:53,316
It was delivered
to Aiko Mizusawa's home today.

548
00:36:54,850 --> 00:36:55,885
Mizusawa's?

549
00:36:56,452 --> 00:36:57,687
According to the dealer,

550
00:36:58,220 --> 00:37:00,890
she talked about how
she was going to start

551
00:37:00,956 --> 00:37:02,992
a shop with her friends.

552
00:37:05,528 --> 00:37:07,997
And she seemed so happy.

553
00:37:12,768 --> 00:37:14,036
Mizusawa

554
00:37:14,870 --> 00:37:18,274
hadn't spent a single yen of that gold.

555
00:37:20,309 --> 00:37:22,345
The money you spent,

556
00:37:23,746 --> 00:37:26,182
she probably intended
to earn and pay it back.

557
00:37:29,285 --> 00:37:31,187
With the dream you had back then.

558
00:37:40,262 --> 00:37:43,432
When we grow up,
let's run a shop together.

559
00:37:43,499 --> 00:37:44,734
What kind of shop?

560
00:37:45,401 --> 00:37:48,504
A place like this,
where all kinds of kids can come.

561
00:37:49,105 --> 00:37:50,172
That sounds good!

562
00:37:56,712 --> 00:37:59,382
It really would've been better
if Togo existed.

563
00:38:13,562 --> 00:38:14,497
Let's go.

564
00:38:30,346 --> 00:38:32,715
You seem curious, so I'll tell you.

565
00:38:33,849 --> 00:38:37,153
When I was a child,
my father chose another woman,

566
00:38:37,219 --> 00:38:38,888
and my parents divorced.

567
00:38:39,922 --> 00:38:42,625
She was flashier
and more beautiful than my mother.

568
00:38:43,959 --> 00:38:48,464
After that, my mother started obsessively
buying clothes and makeup,

569
00:38:48,531 --> 00:38:50,666
and when the money in our house ran out…

570
00:38:52,935 --> 00:38:56,105
She began to force me to shoplift.

571
00:39:01,844 --> 00:39:03,446
If I had made one wrong move,

572
00:39:05,281 --> 00:39:07,516
I could have been one of those four.

573
00:39:12,888 --> 00:39:13,956
But…

574
00:39:14,957 --> 00:39:18,027
your family environment
doesn't decide everything.

575
00:39:20,296 --> 00:39:24,700
The path you walk is up to you.

576
00:39:33,843 --> 00:39:34,810
Hey.

577
00:39:34,877 --> 00:39:36,378
Say something.

578
00:39:38,848 --> 00:39:40,349
I don't have anything to say.

579
00:39:43,686 --> 00:39:44,653
I know that

580
00:39:46,455 --> 00:39:48,090
you won't make a mistake again.

581
00:39:58,400 --> 00:39:59,235
Hey.

582
00:40:00,836 --> 00:40:02,571
What was our dad like?

583
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:05,341
Was he decent?

584
00:40:07,142 --> 00:40:11,180
Dad was hungover
for most of his mornings off.

585
00:40:12,915 --> 00:40:14,550
He did smell like booze.

586
00:40:15,584 --> 00:40:18,387
One time, Mom even poured
hot water on him to wake him up.

587
00:40:18,921 --> 00:40:20,256
Oh, yes, that happened.

588
00:40:20,322 --> 00:40:21,891
You have a good memory!

589
00:40:24,260 --> 00:40:26,061
I've forgotten quite a bit.

590
00:40:28,197 --> 00:40:30,533
I'm forgetting more and more things.

591
00:40:33,936 --> 00:40:35,104
It can't be helped.

592
00:40:35,671 --> 00:40:37,106
You were only five back then.

593
00:40:43,612 --> 00:40:45,581
I'm jealous of you, Makoto.

594
00:41:17,413 --> 00:41:19,515
It's no use. It doesn't fit.

595
00:41:20,716 --> 00:41:22,551
What’s inside?

596
00:42:24,613 --> 00:42:27,683
Few dads would make their kids
something like this.

597
00:42:34,623 --> 00:42:35,591
Minoru?

598
00:42:37,159 --> 00:42:38,427
Makoto.

599
00:42:38,494 --> 00:42:39,862
You saw it from here, right?

600
00:42:39,928 --> 00:42:41,296
I don't care about that!

601
00:42:41,997 --> 00:42:43,599
Let me hear your side. Hey!

602
00:42:43,666 --> 00:42:45,868
-I'm busy, go home.
-No!

603
00:42:47,236 --> 00:42:48,303
That guy…

604
00:42:49,672 --> 00:42:51,907
I wonder what he wanted to hear from Dad?

605
00:42:57,613 --> 00:42:59,481
I'll try going to Fumi's too.

606
00:43:00,082 --> 00:43:01,984
I'll talk to the factory manager too.

607
00:43:10,092 --> 00:43:10,926
What’s wrong?

608
00:43:47,896 --> 00:43:48,964
If we investigate further,

609
00:43:49,031 --> 00:43:50,999
<i>we might find out things</i>
<i>we don't want to know.</i>

610
00:43:51,066 --> 00:43:53,168
<i>Why was Dad complicit</i>
<i>in something like that?</i>

611
00:43:53,235 --> 00:43:54,436
I killed them.

612
00:43:55,003 --> 00:43:56,071
<i>He won't speak at all.</i>

613
00:43:56,138 --> 00:43:57,840
<i>You have a hidden agenda, don't you?</i>

614
00:43:57,906 --> 00:43:59,041
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.

